The '''Hoppou''' avatar, refers to a humanoid character based on the [https://en.kancollewiki.net/Northern_Princess Northern Princess] from the video game series [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kantai_Collection Kantai Collection]. These avatars are usually short and around three to four feet tall with pale skin and distinctively large round eyes. The original Hoppou base model wears black metal necklace hiding her mouth, white cloth mittens, black metal bracelets on hands and feet, and two black metal hairbands. Her attire includes a white dress and long flowing white hair. The character's eyes are typically colored red or orange.

=Popularity of the Hoppou Avatar=

The original Hoppou base model was created by uploading a 3D, MMD model of the Northern Princess to VRChat.
Despite the similarities between this VRChat avatar and its Kantai Collection counterpart, there are some notable differences. Most prominently, the large eyes on the in-game model have contributed to its popularity. This particularity has led to a unique role for these avatars in VRChat communities, when multiple users wearing Hoppou avatars stare directly into another user's eyes, it can provoke humorous reactions of fear.

This unintended consequence helped the growth and formation of groups based around these avatars.

==Hoppou Raids and Communities==

Hoppou communities organized themselves around a phenomenon known as "Hoppou Raids," where multiple users would gather to interact using their Hoppou avatars. It's worth noting that, in VRChat, these Hoppou creations have developed their role-playing narratives distinct from those found within Kantai Collection.

The popularity of the Hoppou base model surged in 2017 due to viral videos showcasing "Hoppou Moth Raid" on random public lobbies, such as NadditionVR's video <ref>[https://youtu.be/-l3QBaWS8Hk Hoppou Moth Raid on random public lobbies]</ref>, and "Hoppou Raid On Xigneon VRChat 2017" by Cutie Corinne <ref>[https://youtu.be/yw8AYAwu44M Hoppou Raid On Xigneon VRChat 2017]</ref>. 

[[File:HoppouRaiding.webp|thumb|A Hoppou raid in the Great Pug West.]]

==A large collection of variations over time==

One factor contributing to the enduring popularity of Hoppou is its vast collection of model variations over the years. The base model has undergone numerous updates, modifications, and reinterpretations by content creators within VRChat. 

[[File:HoppouVariants.webp|thumb|Some Hoppou avatar variants.]]

Well-known streamers have used variation of the Hoppou base model in their VRChat content.

